ext-data-256175010174.Name: Additional Information
ext-data-256175010174.Value:
• Patients received oxaliplatin 85 mg/m^2 and leucovorin 200 mg/m^2, each as a 2-hour intravenous infusion, followed by fluorouracil (FU) 2,600 mg/m^2 as a 24-hour continuous infusion every 2 weeks.
  • Antiemetic prophylaxis was given according to local protocols.
  • The prophylactic use of growth factors was not permitted.
  • Treatment was continued until disease progression, unacceptable toxicity, patient’s refusal, or physician’s decision.
  • The dose of FU was reduced by 20% for diarrhea or mucositis exceeding National Cancer Institute Common Toxicity Criteria (NCI-CTC) grade 2.
  • FU was reduced by 20% for NCI-CTC grade 4 neutropenia or thrombocytopenia.
  • Oxaliplatin dose modifications were performed as described previously.
  • The median cumulative FU dose per patient was 23,400 mg/m^2.
  • The median cumulative doses per patient for oxaliplatin was 759.5 mg/m^2.

ext-data-25617505254.Name: Additional Information
ext-data-25617505254.Value:
• Patients received cisplatin 50 mg/m^2 as a 2-hour infusion every 2 weeks combined with leucovorin 200 mg/m^2 as a 2-hour infusion and fluorouracil (FU) 2,000 mg/m^2 as a 24-hour infusion every week for 6 weeks followed by a 2-week rest.
  • Antiemetic prophylaxis was given according to local protocols.
  • The prophylactic use of growth factors was not permitted.
  • Treatment was continued until disease progression, unacceptable toxicity, patient’s refusal, or physician’s decision.
  • While receiving cisplatin, patients were hydrated with up to 3,000 mL of normal saline.
  • The dose of FU was reduced by 20% for diarrhea or mucositis exceeding National Cancer Institute Common Toxicity Criteria (NCI-CTC) grade 2.
  • Cisplatin was discontinued for NCI-CTC grade 2 or worse renal toxicity.
  • FU and cisplatin were reduced by 20% for NCI-CTC grade 4 neutropenia or thrombocytopenia.
  • The median cumulative FU dose per patient was 22,167 mg/m^2.
  • The median cumulative doses per patient for cisplatin was 295.2 mg/m^2.

ext-data-31163144248.Name: Inclusion Criteria - Old
ext-data-31163144248.Value:
• Histologically confirmed locally advanced or metastatic adenocarcinoma of the stomach or esophagogastric junction (EGJ)
  • No prior palliative chemotherapy
  • Age more than 18 years
  • Eastern Cooperative Oncology Group performance status <=2
  • Sufficient bone marrow function
  • Creatinine clearance more than 50 mL/min
  • No concurrent uncontrolled medical illness
  • No other current or previous malignancy within the past 5 years (with the exception of squamous cell carcinoma of the skin treated by surgery)

ext-data-31163144258.Name: Exclusion Criteria - Old
ext-data-31163144258.Value:
• Peripheral neuropathy of National Cancer Institute grade >=2 at baseline
  • Brain metastases
  • Inflammatory bowel disease
  • Coronary heart disease
  • Cardiac insufficiency (New York Heart Association classification of heart disease class II through IV)
  • Known hypersensitivity to fluorouracil (FU)
  • Known hypersensitivity to leucovorin
  • Known hypersensitivity to oxaliplatin
  • Known hypersensitivity to cisplatin
  • Pregnant
  • Breast-feeding

Datapoints.Value:
• Patients received oxaliplatin 85 mg/m^2 and leucovorin 200 mg/m^2, each as a 2-hour intravenous infusion, followed by fluorouracil (FU) 2,600 mg/m^2 as a 24-hour continuous infusion every 2 weeks.
  • Antiemetic prophylaxis was given according to local protocols. 
  • The prophylactic use of growth factors was not permitted. 
  • The dose of FU was reduced by 20% for diarrhea or mucositis exceeding National Cancer Institute Common Toxicity Criteria (NCI-CTC) grade 2.
  • FU was reduced by 20% for NCI-CTC grade 4 neutropenia or thrombocytopenia. 
  • Oxaliplatin dose modifications were performed as described previously.
  • The median cumulative FU dose per patient was 23,400 mg/m^2.
  • The median cumulative doses per patient for oxaliplatin was 759.5 mg/m^2. 
  • Second-line chemotherapy was performed in 51.8% of patients. 
  • Prior Surgery: Surgery, n = 51 (45.6%), Esophagectomy, n = 4 (3.6%), Total Gastrectomy, n = 33 (29.5%), Partial Gastrectomy, n = 14 (12.5%).
  • Prior Adjuvant Therapy: Chemotherapy, n = 3 (2.7%), Radiotherapy, n = 0 (0%).
  • Dose reductions of any drug were required in 31.3% of patients.
